<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="578" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[675,1211,844,947]" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">
DIAGNOSIS. — Shell 
<emphasis box="[882,898,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[904,965,844,868]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="578" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[976,991,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
84% taller than wide. Umbilicus open, narrow and simple. Sculpture lacking, subsutural narrow shoulder present.Protoconch flattened, of 1 whorl. Spire angle 
<emphasis box="[902,918,924,947]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
70°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="15" pageNumber="578" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[674,1212,977,1604]" box="[677,821,977,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[674,1212,977,1604]" box="[677,859,1008,1034]" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[677,859,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">
Shell (
<figureCitation box="[741,851,1008,1034]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="18.[113,124,1612,1630]" captionTargetBox="[125,1197,215,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-39@18.[393,662,771,1055]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIG. 8. — Shells of MD55 naticid species: A-B, Microlinices ombratus n. gen., n. sp. shell of holotype: A, frontal view; B, dorsal view; C-G, Microlinices apiculus n. gen., n. sp.: C-F, holotype: C, apertural view; D, dorsal view; E, right view; F, apical view; G, paratype MZSP 105146; H-K, Microlinices gaiophanis n. gen., n. sp., holotype MNHN: H, apertural view; I, dorsal view; J, right view; K, apical view. Measurements: A, B, W 3.2 mm; C-F, W 5.3 mm; G, W 4.4 mm; H-K, W 5.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5159253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5159253/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">Fig. 8A, B</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[674,1212,977,1604]" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">
Diameter of 
<quantity box="[821,913,1040,1066]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="578" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
; height 
<emphasis box="[1006,1023,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
120% of width; general form somewhat tall turbinoid. Color pale brown. Protoconch flattened, of 1 rounded whorl; surface smooth, eroded; diameter 
<emphasis box="[1047,1064,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1073,1163,1134,1161]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="578" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, occupying 
<emphasis box="[765,781,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
20% of upper shell surface.Teleoconch of 
<emphasis box="[674,691,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
3 whorls; suture marked by subsutural shoulder, performing angle of 
<emphasis box="[899,916,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
110° in relation to whorl’s profile; upper surface of shoulder planar and almost horizontal, occupying 
<emphasis box="[914,931,1294,1319]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
10% of whorl’s area; spire angle 
<emphasis box="[736,752,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
70°. Sculpture absent except for growth lines and axial weak undulations; undulations stronger in umbilicus. Aperture oval, narrow, occupying 
<emphasis box="[679,696,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
55% of shell height and 
<emphasis box="[970,987,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
44% of shell width; outer lip thick, orthocline, simple; inner lip widely concave, upper half covered by thin callus, lower half as thick edge (
<figureCitation box="[893,982,1515,1541]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="18.[113,124,1612,1630]" captionTargetBox="[125,1197,215,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-39@18.[393,662,771,1055]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIG. 8. — Shells of MD55 naticid species: A-B, Microlinices ombratus n. gen., n. sp. shell of holotype: A, frontal view; B, dorsal view; C-G, Microlinices apiculus n. gen., n. sp.: C-F, holotype: C, apertural view; D, dorsal view; E, right view; F, apical view; G, paratype MZSP 105146; H-K, Microlinices gaiophanis n. gen., n. sp., holotype MNHN: H, apertural view; I, dorsal view; J, right view; K, apical view. Measurements: A, B, W 3.2 mm; C-F, W 5.3 mm; G, W 4.4 mm; H-K, W 5.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5159253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5159253/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Umbilicus simple, narrow, open; its aperture occupying 
<emphasis box="[1114,1131,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">c.</emphasis>
6% of lower surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[677,1101,1641,1700]" box="[677,1101,1641,1668]" pageId="15" pageNumber="578">
