<paragraph blockId="17.[113,646,342,495]" box="[113,219,342,368]" pageId="17" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis box="[113,219,342,368]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="580">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[113,646,342,495]" pageId="17" pageNumber="580">
The specific epithet is derived from the Portuguese word 
<emphasis box="[175,241,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="580">ombro</emphasis>
, meaning shoulder, an allusion to the shoulder-like subsutural carina, characteristic of the species.
</paragraph>
